quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  6,122,"Is he who was dead, and We quickened him and appointed for him a light whereby he walketh among mankind, like unto him whose similitude is that he is in darknesses forth from which he cannot come? Even so is made fair-seeming to the infidels that which they are wont to do"
  6,123,"And even so we set up in every town the great ones as its sinners, that they may plot therein. And they plot not but against themselves, and they perceive not"
  6,124,"And whensoever there cometh unto them a sign, they say: we shall not believe until we are vouchsafed the like of that which is vouchsafed unto the apostles of Allah. Allah knoweth best wheresoever to place His apostleship. Anon shall befall those who have sinned vileness before Allah and severe chastisement for that which they were wont to plot"
  6,125,"So whomsoever Allah willeth that he shall guide, He expoundeth his breast for Islam; and whomsoever He willeth that he shall send astray, He maketh his breast strait, narrow, as if he were mounting up into the sky, thus Allah layeth the abomination on those who believe not"
  6,126,"And this is the path of thine Lord, straight. We have surely detailed the revelations unto a people who would be admonished"
  6,127,For them is an abode of peace with their Lord; and He shall be their patron for that which they have been doing
  6,128,"On the Day whereon He will gather them all together: O ye race of genii! surely much ye have gotten out of mankind. And their friends among mankind will say: our Lord! much use some of us made of others, and now we have reached the appointed term which Thou appointedest for us. He will say: the Fire shall be your habitation, therein ye shall be as abiders, save as Allah may will. Verily thy Lord is Wise, Knowing"
  6,129,And thus We shall keep some of the wrong-doers close to others for that which they were wont to earn